<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-15T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="1012" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1012">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2231/451: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-15T13:00:00-04:00">June 15, 1940—1
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>73. Your 103 and 105, June 13 and 14.<note n="55" xml:id="d1012fn1">Telegram No. 105, June 14, not printed.</note> Announcement in
                            general terms of quota restrictions on schedule articles and duty
                            changes was issued by the Department this morning.<note n="56" xml:id="d1012fn2">Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, June 15, 1940, p. 667.</note></p>
                        <pb facs="0882" n="870" xml:id="pg_870"/>
                        <p>Details will be published by Commerce as soon as possible. Please
                            telegraph immediately data on items 900 and 1086<hi rend="italic">b</hi>, and inform us whether statistics in your 103 are for 3 or 6
                            month quotas.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>